<Content
  title="Privacy Policy | Meter Speed Test"
  description="How Meter Speed Test handles your data: test results stay in your browser, no accounts, no tracking. Learn what data is processed when you run an internet speed test."
  path="/privacy"
  heading="Privacy Policy"
  eyebrow="Legal"
  intro="Meter is built to be private by default. This policy explains, in plain language, what happens to your data when you use meterspeedtest.com."
  updated="July 17, 2026"
>
  <h2>The short version</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>We do <strong>not</strong> require an account, name, email or sign-up to use Meter.</li>
    <li>Your speed test history is stored <strong>locally in your browser</strong> — not on our servers.</li>
    <li>We do <strong>not</strong> sell your data or use advertising or cross-site tracking cookies.</li>
    <li>Running a test connects your browser to third-party networks (such as Cloudflare) that necessarily see your IP address to deliver the measurement.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data stored on your device</h2>
  <p>
    Meter saves a few things in your browser’s <code>localStorage</code> so the app works the way you
    expect:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Test history</strong> — the results of tests you run (download, upload, ping and related metrics, plus a timestamp) so you can track performance over time.</li>
    <li><strong>Theme preference</strong> — whether you chose light or dark mode.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    This information never leaves your device unless you deliberately export or share it. You can
    erase it at any time using the <strong>Clear</strong> button in the History section, or by
    clearing your browser’s site data for meterspeedtest.com.
  </p>

  <h2>Data processed when you run a test</h2>
  <p>
    A speed test works by moving real data between your device and measurement servers, so some
    processing by third parties is unavoidable:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Cloudflare.</strong> Tests stream data to and from Cloudflare’s global edge network.
      To route that traffic, Cloudflare processes your IP address and standard connection details.
      This is handled under Cloudflare’s own privacy terms.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Connection information.</strong> To display “your connection” details such as your
      approximate ISP and IP address, Meter requests that information at test time and shows it back
      to you in your browser. We do not retain it on a server.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Google Fonts.</strong> The site loads its typefaces from Google’s font CDN, which means
      your browser makes a request to Google that includes your IP address. This is handled under
      Google’s privacy terms.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Cookies and tracking</h2>
  <p>
    Meter does not use advertising cookies or cross-site tracking pixels. The site relies on
    <code>localStorage</code> (described above) rather than tracking cookies. We do not build
    advertising profiles and we do not sell or rent any information about you.
  </p>

  <h2>Sharing results</h2>
  <p>
    If you use the share or copy-link feature, your result is encoded directly into the link itself.
    Anyone you send that link to can read the numbers contained in it, but the data is not stored on
    a central server — it travels in the URL. Share links only where you’re comfortable revealing the
    result.
  </p>

  <h2>Children’s privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Meter is a general-audience utility and is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly
    collect personal information from children.
  </p>

  <h2>Your choices</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Clear your local history at any time from the History section, or via your browser settings.</li>
    <li>Use private/incognito browsing to prevent any local history from persisting.</li>
    <li>Block third-party font loading with a browser extension if you prefer (the site still works).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy as the product evolves. When we do, we’ll revise the “Last updated”
    date at the top of this page. Significant changes will be reflected here.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact us</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about privacy? Reach us at
    <a href="mailto:privacy@meterspeedtest.com">privacy@meterspeedtest.com</a>, or visit our
    <a href="/contact">Contact page</a>. See also our <a href="/terms">Terms &amp; Conditions</a>.
  </p>
</Content>
